text: Baker Street is a street in London. It is in a part of London which is called Marylebone, London. It forms part of a bigger road called the A41. It is known because of its connection to the fictional detective Sherlock Holmes. He lived at 221B Baker Street. This is not a real address. The street is named after a builder called William Baker. ==Related pages== * Baker Street tube station Category:Roads in London
title: Baker Street
